## Workflow Directory [FIXED]

All OpenCode workflow machinery lives in `.agent/` (hidden, gitignored state) and `plans/` (committed, user-visible).

```
{{PROJECT_NAME}}/
├── AGENTS.md                   ← this file
├── opencode.json               ← workflow configuration
├── plans/                      ← committed to git (backlog markdowns from /plan)
└── .agent/                     ← gitignored workflow machinery
    ├── commands/               ← /createtasks, /implement, /issue, /feature
    ├── agents/                 ← AI agent persona definitions
    ├── skills/                 ← domain knowledge injected per-command
    ├── backends/               ← workflow backend implementation
    └── lib/                    ← shared Node.js utilities (backend-loader)
        └── state/              ← gitignored runtime state
            ├── issues/
            ├── tasks/
            └── counter.json
```

Use `/issue`, `/createtasks`, and `/implement` to drive all workflow.

